    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn2.5:1.1",
          "pli": "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. ",
          "en": "At Sāvatthī. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.5:1.2",
          "pli": "Atha kho dāmali devaputto abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇo kevalakappaṃ jetavanaṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. ",
          "en": "Then, late at night, the glorious god Dāmali, lighting up the entire Jeta’s Grove, went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.5:1.3",
          "pli": "Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho dāmali devaputto bhagavato santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: ",
          "en": "and recited this verse in the Buddha’s presence: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.5:2.1",
          "pli": "“Karaṇīyametaṃ brāhmaṇena, ",
          "en": "“This is what should be done by a brahmin: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.5:2.2",
          "pli": "Padhānaṃ akilāsunā; ",
          "en": "unrelenting striving. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.5:2.3",
          "pli": "Kāmānaṃ vippahānena, ",
          "en": "Then, with the giving up of sensual pleasures, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.5:2.4",
          "pli": "Na tenāsīsate bhavan”ti. ",
          "en": "they won’t hope to be reborn.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.5:3.1",
          "pli": "“Natthi kiccaṃ brāhmaṇassa, ",
          "en": "“The brahmin has nothing left to do,” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.5:3.2",
          "pli": "(dāmalīti bhagavā) ",
          "en": "said the Buddha to Dāmali, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.5:3.3",
          "pli": "Katakicco hi brāhmaṇo; ",
          "en": "“for they’ve completed their task. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.5:3.4",
          "pli": "Yāva na gādhaṃ labhati nadīsu, ",
          "en": "So long as a person fails to gain a footing in the river, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.5:3.5",
          "pli": "Āyūhati sabbagattebhi jantu; ",
          "en": "they strive with every limb. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.5:3.6",
          "pli": "Gādhañca laddhāna thale ṭhito yo, ",
          "en": "But someone who has gained a footing and stands on dry land "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.5:3.7",
          "pli": "Nāyūhatī pāragato hi sova. ",
          "en": "need not strive, for they have reached the far shore. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.5:4.1",
          "pli": "Esūpamā dāmali brāhmaṇassa, ",
          "en": "Dāmali, this is a simile for the brahmin, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.5:4.2",
          "pli": "Khīṇāsavassa nipakassa jhāyino; ",
          "en": "alert, a meditator who has ended defilements. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.5:4.3",
          "pli": "Pappuyya jātimaraṇassa antaṃ, ",
          "en": "Since they’ve reached the end of rebirth and death, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.5:4.4",
          "pli": "Nāyūhatī pāragato hi so”ti. ",
          "en": "they need not strive, for they have reached the far shore.”"
        }
      ],
